## 11. Supabase Client — `services/supabase_client.py` (554 lines)

**File:** [supabase_client.py](file:///Users/likhith./Veliora.AI_backend./services/supabase_client.py)

Wraps the synchronous `supabase-py` SDK with async-safe patterns.

**Thread-Pool Offloading:** All Supabase operations use `await asyncio.to_thread(sync_call)` to prevent blocking the ASGI event loop. This is critical because the Supabase Python SDK uses synchronous `httpx` under the hood.

**Key Functions:**
| Function | Table | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `get_user_profile(uid)` | `users` | Fetch user profile data |
| `update_user_profile(uid, data)` | `users` | Update profile fields |
| `get_chat_history(uid, bid, limit)` | `messages` | Fetch recent messages |
| `save_messages_batch(messages)` | `messages` | Batch insert messages |
| `get_diary_entries(uid, bid, limit)` | `diaries` | Fetch diary entries |
| `create_game_session(data)` | `user_game_sessions` | Create game session record |
| `update_game_session(sid, data)` | `user_game_sessions` | Update game status |
| `get_games_by_archetype(archetype)` | `games` | Fetch game catalog |
| `log_emotion_telemetry(data)` | `emotion_telemetry` | Persist emotion readings |
| `upload_to_storage(bucket, bytes, path)` | Storage | Upload files to Supabase Storage |

