## 16. Activity UX Helpers — `activities.py` (66 lines)

**File:** [activities.py](file:///Users/likhith./Veliora.AI_backend./activities.py)

In-memory stateful helpers for game/activity UX:
- **Satisfaction detection** — Scans user messages for completion keywords (`"enough"`, `"done"`, `"finished"`) to gracefully end activities
- **Cooldown system** — Prevents immediate repeat of the same activity (300s cooldown per `(username, persona, activity)` tuple)
- **Continuation detection** — Detects user wanting more (`"more"`, `"next"`, `"continue"`)

> **Note:** Per-process in-memory state. For multi-instance deployments, must be migrated to Redis.

